{
  "work_slug": "unknown-work",
  "audio_file": "audio-01",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_01_carroll.mp3",
  "page_start_sec": 0.0,
  "page_end_sec": 242.94,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 0.9,
      "text": "CHAPTER I."
    },
    {
      "start": 1.06,
      "end": 3.08,
      "text": "ALICE'S ADVENTURES IN WONDERLAND."
    },
    {
      "start": 3.3400000000000003,
      "end": 4.86,
      "text": "This is a LibriVox recording."
    },
    {
      "start": 5.16,
      "end": 7.4,
      "text": "All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain."
    },
    {
      "start": 7.64,
      "end": 8.12,
      "text": "For more"
    },
    {
      "start": 8.12,
      "end": 9.52,
      "text": "information or to volunteer,"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.74,
      "end": 11.66,
      "text": "please visit LibriVox.org."
    },
    {
      "start": 12.34,
      "end": 13.94,
      "text": "Recording by Eric Leach."
    },
    {
      "start": 16.34,
      "end": 19.16,
      "text": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland by Lewis Carroll."
    },
    {
      "start": 19.9,
      "end": 20.58,
      "text": "Proem."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.580000000000002,
      "end": 26.44,
      "text": "Tis two score years since Carroll's art with topsy-turvy magic sent Alice wondering through"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.44,
      "end": 28.16,
      "text": "a part half comic and half tragic."
    },
    {
      "start": 28.8,
      "end": 29.56,
      "text": "Enchanting Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.84,
      "end": 30.42,
      "text": "black and white,"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.46,
      "end": 31.34,
      "text": "has made your deeds"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.34,
      "end": 31.78,
      "text": "perennial,"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.92,
      "end": 35.54,
      "text": "and not save chaos and old night can part you now from Tenniel."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.94,
      "end": 36.9,
      "text": "But still you"
    },
    {
      "start": 36.9,
      "end": 37.52,
      "text": "are a type,"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.6,
      "end": 39.56,
      "text": "and based in truth like Lear and Hamlet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 39.64,
      "end": 41.76,
      "text": "and types may be redraped to taste"
    },
    {
      "start": 41.76,
      "end": 43.28,
      "text": "in cloth of gold or camlet."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.46,
      "end": 45.38,
      "text": "Here comes a fresh costumier then,"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.54,
      "end": 47.04,
      "text": "that taste may gain a wrinkle"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.04,
      "end": 50.66,
      "text": "from him who drew with such deft pen the rags of Rip Van Winkle."
    },
    {
      "start": 51.28,
      "end": 52.22,
      "text": "Austin Dobson."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.34,
      "end": 56.02,
      "text": "All in the golden afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 56.44,
      "end": 57.54,
      "text": "Full leisurely we glide,"
    },
    {
      "start": 57.74,
      "end": 61.2,
      "text": "for both our oars with little skill by little arms are plied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.3,
      "end": 64.66,
      "text": "while little hands make vain pretense our wanderings to guide."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.48,
      "end": 66.04,
      "text": "Ah,"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.04,
      "end": 66.56,
      "text": "cruel three,"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.62,
      "end": 67.52,
      "text": "in such an hour,"
    },
    {
      "start": 67.56,
      "end": 68.92,
      "text": "beneath such dreamy weather,"
    },
    {
      "start": 69.06,
      "end": 70.5,
      "text": "to beg a tale of breath"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.5,
      "end": 72.42,
      "text": "too weak to stir the tiniest feather."
    },
    {
      "start": 72.68,
      "end": 75.62,
      "text": "Yet what can one poor voice avail against three"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.62,
      "end": 76.26,
      "text": "tongues together?"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.8,
      "end": 80.84,
      "text": "Imperious Prima flashes forth her edict to begin it."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.94,
      "end": 82.08,
      "text": "In gentler tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 82.2,
      "end": 83.06,
      "text": "Secunda hopes there"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.06,
      "end": 84.16,
      "text": "will be nonsense in it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.2,
      "end": 86.16,
      "text": "while Tertia interrupts the tale."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.44,
      "end": 87.54,
      "text": "Not more than once a minute."
    },
    {
      "start": 88.74000000000001,
      "end": 90.28,
      "text": "Anon to sudden silence one,"
    },
    {
      "start": 90.44,
      "end": 91.64,
      "text": "in fancy they pursue,"
    },
    {
      "start": 91.9,
      "end": 93.6,
      "text": "the dream-child moving through a land"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.6,
      "end": 94.8,
      "text": "of wonders wild and new."
    },
    {
      "start": 95.1,
      "end": 97.14,
      "text": "In friendly chat with bird or beast,"
    },
    {
      "start": 97.3,
      "end": 98.54,
      "text": "and half believe it true."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.22,
      "end": 102.4,
      "text": "And ever as the story drained the wells of fancy dry,"
    },
    {
      "start": 102.6,
      "end": 104.92,
      "text": "and faintly strove that weary one"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.92,
      "end": 106.2,
      "text": "to put the subject by,"
    },
    {
      "start": 106.4,
      "end": 107.66,
      "text": "the rest next time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 107.74,
      "end": 109.82,
      "text": "it is next time the happy voices cry."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.44,
      "end": 112.28,
      "text": "Thus grew the tale of Wonderland,"
    },
    {
      "start": 112.42,
      "end": 113.0,
      "text": "thus slowly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 113.14,
      "end": 113.78,
      "text": "one by one,"
    },
    {
      "start": 114.0,
      "end": 115.78,
      "text": "its quaint events were hammered out,"
    },
    {
      "start": 115.84,
      "end": 116.42,
      "text": "and now they are."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.42,
      "end": 116.42,
      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "start": 116.42,
      "end": 116.42,
      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "start": 116.42,
      "end": 116.42,
      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "start": 116.44,
      "end": 116.98,
      "text": "The tale is done,"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.12,
      "end": 120.12,
      "text": "and home we steer a merry crew beneath the setting sun."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.22,
      "end": 121.66,
      "text": "Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 121.8,
      "end": 122.94,
      "text": "a childish story take,"
    },
    {
      "start": 123.08,
      "end": 124.12,
      "text": "and with a gentle hand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 124.32,
      "end": 126.08,
      "text": "lay it where childhood's dreams are"
    },
    {
      "start": 126.08,
      "end": 127.6,
      "text": "twined in memory's mystic band,"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.82,
      "end": 131.16,
      "text": "like pilgrim's withered wreath of flowers plucked in a far-off"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.16,
      "end": 131.4,
      "text": "land."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.2,
      "end": 134.94,
      "text": "Chapter One,"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.1,
      "end": 136.04,
      "text": "Down the Rabbit Hole"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.54,
      "end": 142.36,
      "text": "Alice was beginning to get very tired of sitting by her sister on the bank,"
    },
    {
      "start": 142.46,
      "end": 143.18,
      "text": "and of having nothing"
    },
    {
      "start": 143.18,
      "end": 143.6,
      "text": "to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 143.82,
      "end": 146.42,
      "text": "Once or twice she had peeped into the book her sister was reading."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.44,
      "end": 148.88,
      "text": "But it had no pictures or conversations in it."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.94,
      "end": 150.3,
      "text": "And what is the use of a book,"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.32,
      "end": 150.8,
      "text": "thought Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.94,
      "end": 152.16,
      "text": "without pictures or conversations?"
    },
    {
      "start": 152.9,
      "end": 155.14,
      "text": "So she was considering in her own mind,"
    },
    {
      "start": 155.22,
      "end": 156.52,
      "text": "as well as she could,"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.58,
      "end": 158.96,
      "text": "for the hot day made her feel very sleepy and stupid,"
    },
    {
      "start": 159.2,
      "end": 163.86,
      "text": "whether the pleasure of making a daisy chain would be worth the trouble of getting up and picking the daisies."
    },
    {
      "start": 163.98,
      "end": 164.7,
      "text": "When suddenly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 164.82,
      "end": 167.12,
      "text": "a white rabbit with pink eyes ran close by her."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.9,
      "end": 170.12,
      "text": "There was nothing so very remarkable in that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 170.18,
      "end": 173.8,
      "text": "nor did Alice think it so very much out of the way to hear the rabbit say to itself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 174.04,
      "end": 174.52,
      "text": "Oh dear,"
    },
    {
      "start": 174.64,
      "end": 175.1,
      "text": "oh dear,"
    },
    {
      "start": 175.22,
      "end": 176.2,
      "text": "I shall be too late."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.88,
      "end": 178.46,
      "text": "When she thought it over afterwards,"
    },
    {
      "start": 178.68,
      "end": 181.3,
      "text": "it occurred to her that she ought to have wondered at this,"
    },
    {
      "start": 181.38,
      "end": 183.04,
      "text": "but at the time it all seemed quite natural."
    },
    {
      "start": 183.42,
      "end": 187.84,
      "text": "But when the rabbit actually took a watch out of its waistcoat pocket and looked at it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 187.86,
      "end": 188.64,
      "text": "and then hurried on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 188.96,
      "end": 190.08,
      "text": "Alice started to her feet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 190.18,
      "end": 196.5,
      "text": "for it flashed across her mind that she had never before seen a rabbit with either a waistcoat pocket or a watch to take out of it."
    },
    {
      "start": 196.64,
      "end": 197.98,
      "text": "And burning with curiosity,"
    },
    {
      "start": 198.16,
      "end": 199.7,
      "text": "she ran across the field after it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 199.78,
      "end": 203.34,
      "text": "and was just in time to see it pop down a large rabbit hole under the hedge."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.38,
      "end": 205.36,
      "text": "In another moment,"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.48,
      "end": 206.18,
      "text": "down went Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.2,
      "end": 206.48,
      "text": "Alice was in a state of shock,"
    },
    {
      "start": 206.48,
      "end": 206.48,
      "text": "and she was not sure what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.48,
      "end": 206.78,
      "text": "She was so shocked that she ran to Alice after it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 206.84,
      "end": 209.66,
      "text": "never once considering how in the world she was to get out again."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.2,
      "end": 212.96,
      "text": "The rabbit hole went straight on like a tunnel for some way,"
    },
    {
      "start": 213.04,
      "end": 214.44,
      "text": "and then dipped suddenly down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 214.66,
      "end": 221.42,
      "text": "so suddenly that Alice had not a moment to think about stopping herself before she found herself falling down what seemed to be a very deep well."
    },
    {
      "start": 222.3,
      "end": 224.0,
      "text": "Either the well was very deep,"
    },
    {
      "start": 224.0,
      "end": 225.4,
      "text": "or she fell very slowly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 225.6,
      "end": 228.16,
      "text": "for she had plenty of time as she went down to look about her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 228.26,
      "end": 230.14,
      "text": "and to wonder what was going to happen next."
    },
    {
      "start": 230.66,
      "end": 230.92,
      "text": "First,"
    },
    {
      "start": 231.04,
      "end": 233.56,
      "text": "she tried to look down and make out what she was coming to,"
    },
    {
      "start": 233.68,
      "end": 235.4,
      "text": "but it was too dark to see anything."
    },
    {
      "start": 235.78,
      "end": 236.18,
      "text": "Then she looked down and found Alice in the middle of the field."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.2,
      "end": 239.94,
      "text": "Then she looked at the sides of the well and noticed that they were filled with cupboards and bookshelves."
    },
    {
      "start": 240.1,
      "end": 242.94,
      "text": "Here and there she saw maps and pictures hung upon pegs."
    }
  ]
}